WingTask Configuration Instructions
-------------------------

Please follow the instructions below to configure Taskwarrior to sync
with WingTask Taskserver.


Dependencies
------------
You will need to install Taskwarrior 2.5.1 or newer.

Installation options for your platform:

https://taskwarrior.org/download/


Basic Installation
------------------

An installation script is provided that will configure Taskwarrior
for sync with WingTask server:

  [1] $ chmod +x install.sh
  [2] $ ./install.sh

These command are explained below:

  1. Make install script executable.
  2. Execute install scripts.

Install script will do the following:

  [1] $ cp -r wingtask_certs $HOME/.wingtask_certs
  [2] $ task config 'taskd.server' 'app.wingtask.com:53589'
  [3] $ task config 'taskd.key' '~/.wingtask_certs/artin2007majidi@gmail.com.key.pem'
  [4] $ task config 'taskd.ca'  '~/.wingtask_certs/letsencrypt_root_cert.pem'
  [5] $ task config 'taskd.certificate' '~/.wingtask_certs/artin2007majidi@gmail.com.cert.pem'
  [6] $ task config 'taskd.credentials' 'WingTask/artin2007majidi@gmail.com/5cfe22f3-dd9c-4d59-876f-21d43ed011e5'


These commands are explained below:

  1. Backup .taskrc

  2. Copy wingtask cert files to a hidden directory in user $HOME

  3. Invoke task config to set taskd.server

  4. Invoke task config to set taskd.key to key generated for user.

  5. Invoke task config to set taskd.ca to intermediate root certificate

  6. Invoke task config to set taskd.certificate to cert generated for user.

  7. Invoke task config to set 'taskd.credentials' with server identity for user.


"sync" command
--------------

After install script is invoked taskwarrior is configured to sync local
task data up to WingTask servers:

NOTE: Install script does not execute sync and this command must be done
manually.

There are two sync commands:

  [1] $ task sync init
  [2] $ task sync

  1. task sync init is for first time sync only.
  2. task sync is for all subsequent sync.

Troubleshooting
---------------
Taskwarrior provides a doc for troubleshooting common issues with
sync:

https://taskwarrior.org/docs/taskserver/troubleshooting-sync.html

Two particular commands are handy for diagnosing problems:

  $ task diagnostics

  Has a section showing the configuration of Taskwarrior. Should
  include all of the configuration set in the install script.

  $ task rc.debug=1 rc.debug.tls=2 sync

  This is the sync command run in verbal debug mode.

I can provide additonal help, please email me:

tim@wingtask.com

